.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E23C73AEDA48F112BD8DB8F4F372DA37" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<materialsCitation id="CE9A50CD86F796EC3E139AA0B3A10DF0" collectingDate="2017-01-01" collectingDateMax="2017-12-31" collectingDateMin="2017-01-01" country="USA" location="Utah" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Utah" typeStatus="holotype">
<collectingCountry id="3562F0B4E8C6B0CD0B8B09806CA376A7" name="United States of America">USA</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion id="4A077053C5257394AFD5588AD08349BF" country="United States of America" name="Utah">Utah</collectingRegion>
. Beaver, 1877, Palmer s.n. (
<typeStatus id="9276B2C7D4650D84358A8732FDABD119">holotype</typeStatus>
: GH, GH00091198 [GH website image)]; probable isotype: ISC, ISC-v-0000867 [JSTOR image]
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E705894DC35DE5688033EA9FBA9E5FE" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
The correct name for this taxon at the rank of species has been the source of confusion. With the earlier name 
<taxonomicName id="C668E3EC772644B3AE99F674FEFE5D8B" authorityName="Dougl. ex Benth" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Penstemon suffruticosus" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffruticosus">
<emphasis id="716581CBBD23F36A770263E0EA11B5F1" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Penstemon suffruticosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Douglas ex Benth. blocking transfer of A. 
<normalizedToken id="0B545150FA54B02C002D429CF4192E85" originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
varietal epithet 
<taxonomicName id="E19635FB4F6A76E55E7BD2B5DA3B31B5" authorityName="Dougl. ex Benth" authorityYear="1846" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="suffruticosus" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="suffruticosus">
<emphasis id="7DC930E1EF37C778B2516AB6D6510C99" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">suffruticosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the rank of species, 
<bibRefCitation id="D97456E275358FA2A77A9FC7B5D8F4FF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478562" author="Rydberg, PA" journalOrPublisher="Club" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="499 - 513" refId="B7" refString="Rydberg, PA, 1901. Studies on the Rocky Mountain flora.-VI. Bull. Torrey Bot. Club 28: 499 - 513, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2478562" title="Studies on the Rocky Mountain flora. - VI. Bull. Torrey Bot." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2478562" volume="28" year="1901">Rydberg (1901)</bibRefCitation>
published 
<taxonomicName id="F130923759E03EC709E0C16FBC3671E5" genus="P." lsidName="P. suffrutescens" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis id="CB4429AD6A8A2632A41D9245C3FEB0DD" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in an attempt to provide a substitute. However, in doing so, he flagged 
<taxonomicName id="B78D7FF404298440277DB3233F54CBF4" genus="P." lsidName="P. suffrutescens" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis id="D92B491D96C122511B97A15203F5FBEA" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species (sp. nov.). He also provided a brief diagnosis and cited a specimen (
<collectingCountry id="195C2D71BB2CCE60C956704B525929D2" name="United States of America">USA</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion id="E8C297BF7A329344608EF02F6A217477" country="United States of America" name="Colorado">Colorado</collectingRegion>
. Ridgway, woods, altitude 
<quantity id="607BCD3C4EC2BF40867B40EBEED6CF6A" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" unit="ft" value="7500.0">7500 ft</quantity>
, 
<date id="D36F52D3FC0D19FC0B3E6DE63196AD1A" value="1895-06-20">20 Jun 1895</date>
, F. Tweedy 170; 
<typeStatus id="7C6BDF4ECAC7295F8026539C1FAEE102">holotype</typeStatus>
: NY, NY00130526 [NY website image]) different from that of 
<normalizedToken id="A1947FCF08067F7A63C20B7433AB30DC" originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
type for 
<taxonomicName id="20867C88C6B0425DB30E75571BC94015" genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
. 
<normalizedToken id="BC2195A2F67E17C3336585E52772C43E" originalValue="Rydberg’s">Rydberg's</normalizedToken>
name must be considered a validly published species name-not an avowed substitute for 
<normalizedToken id="BCADB64E9CE27D00F4026870E52BE213" originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
name. As noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="35E335DCE183358E6D4BE2EE765DE985" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" author="Holmgren, NH" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="104 - 107" refId="B2" refString="Holmgren, NH, 1979. Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons. Brittonia 31: 104 - 107, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" title="Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" volume="31" year="1979">Holmgren (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, the specimen cited by Rydberg is referable to 
<taxonomicName id="84FE4BCABD6656DB0F9D38F2C371BD5A" genus="P." lsidName="P. crandallii" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="crandallii">
<emphasis id="0A924D7FC8DB90D7DD13EE350D1CF322" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. crandallii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where 
<taxonomicName id="6F06F81B67AF19C1506F50E41831BA04" genus="P." lsidName="P. suffrutescens" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="suffrutescens">
<emphasis id="1B8E5D62B92C13836B72B86B4331CA43" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. suffrutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be placed as a synonym.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B98B6114004E7C61940E53FEE00B954D" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">
<bibRefCitation id="F3EA351CC2D32B98451943990377CA05" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1086/328257" author="Nelson, A" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Rocky Mountain Herbarium" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="21 - 35" refId="B5" refString="Nelson, A, 1902. . Contributions from the Rocky Mountain Herbarium III: 21 - 35, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1086/328257" url="https://doi.org/10.1086/328257" volume="III" year="1902">Nelson (1902)</bibRefCitation>
published 
<taxonomicName id="E8045C47B840A230489924C3B151EBF9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Penstemon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Penstemon xylus" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xylus">
<emphasis id="F59941CDEE184B8324FF78F1E8254089" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">Penstemon xylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and clearly stated it was a new name (nom. nov.) for 
<normalizedToken id="B2D9E2AA5B00B01311EB4FC652F316D3" originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="656650C27A8D4BA331FA5B897D237158" genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
. Nelson cited a specimen (
<collectingCountry id="5040EF0E9699AEF92F0FF1E445147552" name="United States of America">USA</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingRegion id="DBF2540B93E13D14848074231240B336" country="United States of America" name="Colorado">Colorado</collectingRegion>
. Sapinero, 1898, H.N. Wheeler 446 [COLO, COLO00396499 [JSTOR image], NY, NY00130556 [NY website image], RM, RM0004372 [JSTOR image]) that he believed was referable to A. 
<normalizedToken id="B06A135B2DF547AFB201260A20EA368B" originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
concept of 
<taxonomicName id="EC1121D36782B0917476682DF5A3ECC4" genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
. However, it too is referable to 
<taxonomicName id="DEE32C5EA04D5200D696A21F38F17B3A" genus="P." lsidName="P. crandallii" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="crandallii">
<emphasis id="54BAD71501D74A5B7ECEC8A918BCB48E" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. crandallii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="61F30EEF214F337205EB2BD440CC0669" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" author="Holmgren, NH" journalOrPublisher="Brittonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="38" pagination="104 - 107" refId="B2" refString="Holmgren, NH, 1979. Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons. Brittonia 31: 104 - 107, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" title="Nomenclatural changes in some Intermountain penstemons." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/2806680" volume="31" year="1979">Holmgren (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, believing that neither 
<normalizedToken id="DB0904E03A4F85D00D81D1D9FE578EEF" originalValue="Rydberg’s">Rydberg's</normalizedToken>
nor 
<normalizedToken id="F5C6E8751E3CD70543BA0B12C2FABFF3" originalValue="Nelson’s">Nelson's</normalizedToken>
name could be applied to 
<normalizedToken id="70DB8C656C903A40E55C4675F759C91E" originalValue="Gray’s">Gray's</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="310AE93EFDE0B7CED1398C2D6EACB4D2" genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
because of the specimens cited by each author, published 
<taxonomicName id="4E087912A82F4D9EF506ED421A2B1598" genus="P." lsidName="P. tusharensis" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="tusharensis">
<emphasis id="E8798DC80E837020674804857723B6D5" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. tusharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an avowed substitute. In spite of Nelson having cited a specimen that is not referable to 
<taxonomicName id="1484A85441A68CAAFDBC1343ACE8CAA6" genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="076F81592179AB1E8E2B418396EADEB2" genus="P." lsidName="P. xylus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="xylus">
<emphasis id="DFB6BA78CBE0DDBD3187B079C679D720" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. xylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must stand as the avowed substitute for 
<taxonomicName id="12DB1FEBF942B8B1BFA776E6C790E7A1" genus="P." lsidName="P. caespitosus subsp. var. var. suffruticosus" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="variety" species="caespitosus" subSpecies="var." variety="suffruticosus">P. caespitosus var. suffruticosus</taxonomicName>
at the rank of species, making 
<taxonomicName id="811C7A5E09FECE1B9E255B1DB0FEF9B7" genus="P." lsidName="P. tusharensis" pageId="4" pageNumber="37" rank="species" species="tusharensis">
<emphasis id="4CF91F0F1A771FBCE3D93D91C07E8F81" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="37">P. tusharensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illegitimate and superfluous.
</paragraph>
